messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hey, hey, I need a sheriff.
What's the location of the emergency?
The corner of Reef and Weimus.
What's going on there?
I got three people attacking people.
They're attacking kids?
Yes, sir.
Okay, is there any way you can get the kids away from them?
No, they have four guys here with bats.
I got this kid who was badly injured.
How old are the kids?
I have no idea.
Are they like teenagers or little kids?
They're little kids. Like toddlers.
Hey, come back. You got to stay here, bud.
I know, I know it hurts, my man. I know it hurts.
Hey, I'm getting help over here, okay?
How many kids are injured, sir?
There's one kid. Just one kid.
Do you have an ambulance coming?
Yes, we're getting an ambulance on the way.
Where are the attackers right now?
I got them. They decided to take off. They're on the road somewhere, man.
Is that the child I'm hearing in the background?
Yeah, it is, man.
Okay, sir. Let me get Southwest ambulance on the line with us, okay? Stay on the line, don't hang up.
No, you're not, man. You're not.
I got to.
